[
    {
        "content": "<p>cc <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671004\">@Danilo Krummrich</span> </p>\n<p>It's a bit unfortunate that <code>drm::Device::new()</code> takes <code>T::Data</code>, since <code>T::Data</code> may need the Device to initialize itself.</p>\n<p>Consider this excerpt from the Asahi project:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Device</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">AsahiDriver</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new_no_data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">gpu</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">cfg</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">gpu_gen</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cfg</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">gpu_variant</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compat</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_slice</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hw</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">GpuGen</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">G13</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">12</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">gpu</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">GpuManagerG13V12_3</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">res</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cfg</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"k\">dyn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">gpu</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">GpuManager</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;----------</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">       </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">snip</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">dev_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                    </span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                    </span><span class=\"s\">\"Unsupported GPU/firmware combination ({:?}, {:?}, {:?})</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                    </span><span class=\"n\">cfg</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">gpu_gen</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                    </span><span class=\"n\">cfg</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">gpu_variant</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                    </span><span class=\"n\">compat</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ENODEV</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Arc</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">try_pin_init</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">AsahiData</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">gpu</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clone</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">resources</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">res</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">GFP_KERNEL</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>They added a hack to make this possible, i.e.: <code>drm::Device::new_no_data()</code> and <code>drm::Device::init_data()</code>. I think we should follow suit and somehow allow this upstream.</p>\n<p>How about this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">new_from_closure</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">device</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Device</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">F</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">ARef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">FnOnce</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ARef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">create_drm_device</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clone</span><span class=\"p\">());</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set_data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 499261517,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1739373943
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For me, in particular, this is a problem when initializing the firmware. It's hard to allocate the BO to place the firmware in, since you need the device to create a GEM object, but a drm::Device is not available at this point.</p>",
        "id": 499262867,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1739374248
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This topic was moved here from <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"288089\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Initializing.20a.20drm.3A.3ADevice.20with.20no.20T.3A.3AData\">#General &gt; Initializing a drm::Device with no T::Data</a> by <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"671004\">Danilo Krummrich</span>.</p>",
        "id": 503097123,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1741027122
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"582628\">@Daniel Almeida</span> ,</p>\n<p>Sorry for the delay on this. As discussed in the regular sync meeting, I hacked up something that should solve the issue. Please have a look at [1].</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>\n<p>[1] <a href=\"https://web.git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/dakr/linux.git/log/?h=topic/rust-drm\">https://web.git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/dakr/linux.git/log/?h=topic/rust-drm</a></p>",
        "id": 503097507,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1741027246
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that will still require refactoring for asahi since it uses <code>dev.data()</code> outside of the ioctl implementations. Those are not direct callees but more removed. I'm not sure whether passing data along the call chain or accessing the used resources in a different way is the right solution, probably both on a case by case basis.<br>\nI see that this is used to break the circular dependency between device and initialised device data which was right now only enforced by careful programming.</p>",
        "id": 503205190,
        "sender_full_name": "Janne Grunau",
        "timestamp": 1741076395
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671509\">@Janne Grunau</span> Where else does Asahi use <code>drm::Device::data()</code>?</p>",
        "id": 503210589,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1741078198
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's used in DriverFile::open() and a couple of driver internal functions where I'm not sure that all are called from the ioctls. And even the ones which are are several levels below ioctl functions</p>",
        "id": 503252255,
        "sender_full_name": "Janne Grunau",
        "timestamp": 1741090721
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>DriverFile::open()</code> should indeed also pass the driver data as a separate argument.</p>\n<p>Otherwise, I don't see where you'd need to access <code>drm::Device::data()</code>? IRQs should get it from the private data of the (in case of Asahi) <code>platform::Device</code>.</p>\n<p>IOCTLs should really be the only entry points where the private data from the DRM device should be relevant.</p>",
        "id": 503253295,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1741091044
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi Danilo, I need some time to look at this, it's currently a holiday here in Brazil.</p>",
        "id": 503253824,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1741091198
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671509\">@Janne Grunau</span> Updated the branch to consider <code>DriverFile::open()</code>.</p>",
        "id": 503257623,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1741092301
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sorry, I don't see any issues yet. I was mostly complaining about the driver which used <code>data()</code> in places where it wasn't immediately obvious how to replace them</p>",
        "id": 503281608,
        "sender_full_name": "Janne Grunau",
        "timestamp": 1741098479
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Btw. I went through the Asahi driver and every code path that uses / stores a reference of the DRM device <strong>before</strong> registration, only does so to call the <code>dev_*</code> print macros on the underlying bus device.</p>\n<p>This is a bit of an abuse, because then the driver should rather pass in the bus device, i.e. in the case of Asahi the <code>platform::Device</code>.</p>\n<p>But maybe I just miss the one where it actually needs a DRM device.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671509\">@Janne Grunau</span> Can you point me at some code path that really needs a DRM device before registration, rather than the bus device?</p>",
        "id": 503296536,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1741101984
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I suspected that but never checked after Daniel said tyr has the same requirement</p>",
        "id": 503346519,
        "sender_full_name": "Janne Grunau",
        "timestamp": 1741116273
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671509\">@Janne Grunau</span> Just to clarify, I didn't want to say we don't need what I just implemented, Tyr (and likely other drivers) have a very valid use-case. But I wanted to let you know that likely Asahi doesn't need it as is and should consider passing the bus device instead. :)</p>",
        "id": 503348333,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1741116839
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>understood.<br>\nthe agx driver is now \"rebased\" onto <a href=\"https://web.git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/dakr/linux.git/log/?h=topic/rust-drm\">topic/rust-drm</a> and working. I haven't done the drm device -&gt; platform device replacement yet but I haven't spotted a place where the drm device was needed during initialisation.</p>",
        "id": 503444608,
        "sender_full_name": "Janne Grunau",
        "timestamp": 1741161388
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll do a few more fixups and then push things to drm-misc/topic/rust-drm and send it to the list.</p>",
        "id": 503449222,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1741163015
    }
]